# 01 — Workflow

This rule governs how work enters and exits the checkout-orchestrator repo (IHMS-OMS).
Merged from KB-IHMS [`git-workflow.mdc`](https://github.com/iamkaranvalecha/KB-IHMS/blob/main/.cursor/rules/git-workflow.mdc), [`github-project.mdc`](https://github.com/iamkaranvalecha/KB-IHMS/blob/main/.cursor/rules/github-project.mdc), and [`oms-integration.mdc`](https://github.com/iamkaranvalecha/KB-IHMS/blob/main/.cursor/rules/oms-integration.mdc) (orchestrator-side).

Read [AGENTS.md](../AGENTS.md) for the stable overview; [ROADMAP.md](../ROADMAP.md) for current phase.

---

## Hard rules (from KB-IHMS git-workflow)

- **Never commit on `main` or `master`.** Create or checkout a feature branch first.
- **Never push to `main` or `master`.** Push the feature branch and open a PR.
- **Issue before code.** Create a GitHub issue on [Project #5](https://github.com/users/iamkaranvalecha/projects/5/views/1) *before* the first commit for new work. No PR without a linked issue.
- **"Commit and push"** means: commit on feature branch → push branch → open PR with `Closes #N`. It never means push to `main`.
- **Exception:** push/merge to `main` only when the user explicitly says to push directly to main or merge without a PR.

---

## Repository scope

| Repo | Agent may change? |
|------|-------------------|
| IHMS-OMS (this repo) | Yes — all integration work |
| KB-IHMS | Docs/rules only — cross-repo PR, no assignment code |
| EC-OPS | Never — frozen assignment |

When KB-IHMS docs need updating, open a separate issue and PR in that repo.
Do not bundle KB-IHMS changes with orchestrator feature PRs unless explicitly coordinated.

