## OMS integration phase gates (v4 ROADMAP)

Aligned with KB-IHMS `oms-integration.mdc` — orchestrator owns delivery; IHMS/EC-OPS frozen.

| Phase | Goal | Gate before next phase |
|-------|------|------------------------|
| 0 | Baseline lock | KB-IHMS green; EC-OPS noted; no upstream code changes |
| 1 | Scaffold | `verify.sh` green; DECISION-MATRIX; 4 rules; ROADMAP Phase 1 |
| 2 | Gateway + session + catalog | IhmsClient, EcOpsClient; contract + component tests |
| 3 | Saga + flows | place-hold, confirm, cancel, compensate, reconciliation |
| 4 | React UI | Orchestrator API only; optional dev correlation panel |
| 5 | Full stack + E2E | compose.full.yml; all FAILURE-SCENARIOS rows tested |

Append learnings to [ROADMAP.md](../ROADMAP.md) and [AI-USAGE.md](../AI-USAGE.md) after each gate — not to KB-IHMS unless docs-only cross-repo PR.

### Integration principles (binding)

- **IHMS owns hold lifecycle** — stock deduction, expiry, release, events. Orchestrator coordinates checkout; it does not reimplement hold rules.
- **Contract-first** — integrate via IHMS REST (`POST/GET/DELETE /api/holds`) and optionally RabbitMQ events in Phase 5.
- **Adapter boundary** — all upstream HTTP in `src/gateway/` only; no OMS/IHMS types leaking into UI.
- **Additive upstream changes** — none in frozen repos; orchestrator adapts to published contracts.
- **Quality bar** — `bash scripts/verify.sh` must pass before the next phase starts.

