## Labels and project board

Project board: https://github.com/users/iamkaranvalecha/projects/5/views/1

This is the single source of truth for what to work on (from KB-IHMS `github-project.mdc`).

### Status columns (use exactly)

`Backlog` → `Ready` → `In progress` → `In review` → `Done`

Priority order: P0, then P1, then P2.

### Before starting work

```bash
gh project item-list 5 --owner iamkaranvalecha --format json
```

- Pick the highest-priority item in "Ready" or "In progress". If none exist, ask the user before creating ad-hoc work.
- Read linked issues for acceptance criteria before writing code.
- Scope branches, commits, and PRs to one project item.

### Creating issues

```bash
gh issue create --title "[Phase N] ..." --body "..." --project "IHMS-OMS" \
  --label "priority/p1,size/m,integration/oms"
```

Or use `.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/integration-task.md`.

| Label | Use |
|-------|-----|
| `integration/oms` | All orchestrator integration work (required) |
| `priority/p0` … `priority/p2` | Priority |
| `size/xs` … `size/xl` | Effort |
| `area/backend`, `area/frontend`, `area/docs`, `area/infra` | Scope |
| `phase-1` … `phase-5` | Optional phase filter |
| `documentation` | Docs-only changes |
| `blocked` | Waiting on upstream or user decision |

### Project automation

KB-IHMS `.github/workflows/project-sync.yml` pattern (add to IHMS-OMS when ready):

- **Issues opened/labeled** → add to project, Status = Backlog
- **PR opened** → Status = In review (branch `cursor/{N}-*`)
- **PR merged** → Status = Done on PR and linked issue

Do not manually fight the workflow — set Status via board or rely on automation.

**`PROJECT_PAT` secret:** User-owned Project #5 requires a **classic PAT** with `project`, `read:project`, `repo`, and `read:org` scopes. Fine-grained PATs cannot access user-owned projects. Until set, sync skips gracefully and CI stays green.

